OL,1,D]S737{kkkc5FOrla Guerin: The children  
OL,2,D]S555{jjj25Fof Yemen's forgotten war   
OL,3,D]Suuu{rrzq5F                           
OL,4,T#######################################
OL,5, If suffering had an address, it might  
OL,6, be al-Rasheed Street, in Taiz, a Yemeni
OL,7, city ringed by mountains and rebel     
OL,8, Houthi fighters. On this narrow street 
OL,9, of rough-hewn homes, the young can't   
OL,10, escape a grinding conflict the world   
OL,11, tends to forget.                       
OL,13,FA slight boy with a mop of dark hair   
OL,14,Fleads us down the street, nimbly       
OL,15,Fside-stepping potholes - with his      
OL,16,Fcrutches. Bader al-Harbi is seven years
OL,17,Fold, just a little younger than Yemen's
OL,18,Fwar. His right leg has been amputated  
OL,19,Fabove the knee. The slogan on his      
OL,20,FT-shirt reads "Sport".                 
